                    Section: 12 - Your Shop goes Live!
1 - Now it’s time to get your Domain
Shopify uses shopify in the URL of site by default
You can have a custom domain name
Shopify will host your site and have a custom domain (use of a third party is recommended)
Shopify does not offer e-mail support as part of hosting package
Full tutorial available for setting up custom domains
 - https://help.shopify.com/manual/domains

2 - Let’s talk about customer Emails
Your customers should receive mail from your custom domain
 - Settings -> General -> Store Details -> Customer Email
Domain settings will need to be adjusted to avoid customer emails going to their spam folders
SPF Framework - Sender Policy Framework
SPF will verify your customer email address for the automatic notification emails that your customers receive
You may need to contact your domain provider to make sure that it isn't using DomainKey Identified Mail (DKIM) validation 
Tool available for checking SPF records are set up correctly
 - https://mxtoolbox.com/spf.aspx


3 - Add a Facebook Page
Add a Facebook page as early as possible
Facebook makes it easy for you to reach potential customer
You can add your Facebook page in the customize themes section
Liquid Template can be customised through code to add Facebook links in all areas of your store

4 - Let’s talk about Promoting and Advertising on Facebook
A quick discusion on how to advertise your store using Facebook
Extensive notes on Facebook Advertisng are available at
 - https://github.com/marb61a/Course-Notes/blob/master/Marketing/Digital%20Marketing

5 - Get Mailchimp ready to collect Emails
Using Mailchimp with your store to email users
Shopify has a Mailchimp App in the store
Mailchimp has both a free and a pro version, the free version has enough for most small stores
You will need a Mailchimp account to be able to use the plugin
You will need a list of customers which will synce with Mailchimp
More information is available at the following addresses
 - http://kb.mailchimp.com/integrations/e-commerce/use-mailchimp-for-shopify
 - https://ecommerce.shopify.com/c/ecommerce-marketing/t/what-are-best-practices-for-using-mailchimp-with-shopify-340603
Mailchimp allows for segmenting of cusomers
Full discussion on segmenting customers is available at 
 - https://github.com/marb61a/Course-Notes/blob/master/Marketing/How%20Retargeting%20works
Segmentation will be done differently with each store
Mailchimp allows for extensive customising of email templates


